reviews.review_text:
9.3.85 Starlight Great Sounding audience source, Front-Of-Soundboard!  A high energy show, with great guitar work, but a rough night of remembering lyrics for Jerry.  Mediocre 1st set songlist, but the first 4 songs are worth listening to.  2nd set has some unusual song combos; the words to Cryptical are shaky, but the music is good and the blues covers after Space are excellent.  
Band's performance: 3.5 stars.  Recording:  4.5 stars.

Starlight '85 First show! My mom wrote a note so I could leave high school early to go see the show with my older sister and her boyfriend. I can say unequivocally that night changed my life FOREVER!!! I was completley and totally enomored by the whole scene, espicailly the band.

It was a damn good show and a great nighttime outdoor/camping scene. Truckin' absolutley rocks!!

Went on to see them 130 times...not nearly enough! God I miss those good times but I'm so grateful for having had them. 

Eternally Grateful to Jerry, Bobby and the boys and of course to all my fellow Dead Heads for so many good times.... my love will not fade away!!!
